    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix slice RAN function implementation to handle missing flexric dependencies\n\n### Summary\nThe slice RAN function implementation in the E2 agent was referencing missing flexric library files that are not present in the OAI codebase. When `read_slice_sm()` was called, it would attempt to call `fill_slice_ind_data()` which doesn't exist, causing undefined behavior or compilation issues.\n\nThe issue was that the code was trying to include and use functions from `../../flexric/test/rnd/fill_rnd_data_slice.h` and `../../flexric/src/agent/e2_agent_api.h` which are not part of the standard OAI distribution. This caused the slice monitoring functionality to be broken.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/E2AP/RAN_FUNCTION/CUSTOMIZED/ran_func_slice.c`: \n  - Removed include reference to missing `fill_rnd_data_slice.h`\n  - Replaced `fill_slice_ind_data()` call with informative logging\n  - Updated `write_ctrl_slice_sm()` to avoid accessing missing data structures\n- `openair2/E2AP/RAN_FUNCTION/CUSTOMIZED/ran_func_slice.h`:\n  - Removed include reference to missing `e2_agent_api.h`  \n  - Added minimal forward declaration of `sm_ag_if_ans_t` structure\n\nWithout this fix, calling `read_slice_sm()` would result in either compilation errors due to missing headers, or runtime issues when trying to call the non-existent `fill_slice_ind_data()` function. Now the function provides informative logging when called and returns gracefully without crashing.\n"
}